    "source": "doi:10.1101/2024.06.21.599617",
    "sourceFigure": "Fig. 2a",
    "note": "1P excitation and emission digitized from Lee 2026 Fig. 2a (the blue ASAP6c curves), measured in HEK293-Kir2.1 cells. Excitation rises from ~360 nm with a vibronic shoulder near ~425 nm and a dip near ~455 nm, peaking ~497-500 nm, then falls steeply; its far red edge (beyond ~516 nm) overlaps the emission band and was extended smoothly to baseline. Emission peaks ~520 nm with the characteristic GFP-like red tail. ASAP6c (=ASAP6.3) carries the T203H red-shifting mutation, so it is red-shifted vs ASAP3/ASAP4b and spectrally similar to JEDI-2P (paper text: 'peak excitation at 500 nm vs the 485 nm peak of ASAP3'). Replaces an earlier verbatim ASAP4b copy.",
